title: Windows bachup and restore
content:
I am running windows 11 and every time I go to backup my C: drive my system tells me that "I dont have a Disc to back up fo" ? I am retired now so I dont use a computer as much as I use to. I got this system new 6 months ago. It came with Win 10 on it. I have not explored this system fully yet. All this time I did not know it was not backing up automatically. I do remember on earlier versions of windows they had a function that allow you to see the contents of each drive . It also showed each of the partitions on your drives and showed how much was allicated to Windows , recovery, free space. and so on.... I cant seem to find that function on this system. ??? Can you please try to help me with my problems?

Thank you !!

title: Youtube HDR video overexposed on Mac
content:
When watching a HDR video on Firefox on Mac (in this case, a Mac Mini M4 running Sequoia) - freshly installed, connected to an AOC QHD HDR monitor via USB-C->Displayport cable, the video appears overexposed with large patches of white making the video unwatchable. This applies to all HDR video on Youtube.

Watching the same video on Safari presents no such issues - HDR video plays as expected.

title: Re-Opened to Tabs from a Month Ago - Help to Recover Last Session Post-Crash
content:
My laptop unexpectedly closed Firefox after it crashed and upon a restart I re-opened Firefox, which normally restores all my open windows/tabs from the very last session no problem whenever it force quits due to laptop crashes. But this time when opening, it restored windows/tabs from almost a month ago. I closed Firefox and checked the sessionstore-backups folder: - the recovery-backup files are from the session date I just re-opened with old tabs - the previous.jsonlz4 file is from about a month ago and seems to be the reference point used when restoring tabs rather than my actual last session

Is there any other file or method I could use to recover my actual prior session tabs before it crashed?

I have not re-opened Firefox since quitting the browser after seeing it restored the old tabs.

Thank you in advance!
creator: joshmoon
